---
const questions = [
  {
    id: 'faq-1',
    title: 'How can I protect my business from BEC attacks?',
    answer:
      'To protect your business from BEC attacks, you should educate your employees about the risks of BEC, implement strong email security protocols, and use multi-factor authentication for email accounts. You can also partner with a trusted cyber security provider to help you identify and prevent BEC attacks.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-2',
    title: 'What are the consequences of a successful BEC attack?',
    answer:
      'A successful BEC attack can result in significant financial losses, reputational harm, and legal liability for your business. It is important to take BEC attacks seriously and take steps to protect your organization.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-3',
    title: "What services do you offer to protect against BEC attacks?",
    answer:
      'We offer a range of services to help protect your business from BEC attacks, including email security assessments, employee training and awareness programs, and incident response and investigation services.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-4',
    title: "How do I know if my business has been targeted by a BEC attack?",
    answer:
      'Some common signs of a BEC attack include unusual or urgent requests for money or sensitive information, changes to vendor or employee information, and suspicious email addresses or domains. If you suspect that your business has been targeted by a BEC attack, you should contact a trusted cyber security provider immediately.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-5',
    title: 'What are some common types of BEC attacks?',
    answer:
      'Some common types of BEC attacks include CEO fraud, invoice fraud, vendor compromise, attorney impersonation, domain spoofing, and data theft. Attackers use a variety of tactics to trick employees into transferring money or sensitive information.',
  },
  {
    id: 'faq-6',
    title: 'What should I do if my business has been targeted by a BEC attack?',
    answer:
      'If your business has been targeted by a BEC attack, you should contact a trusted cyber security provider immediately. They can help you contain the incident, investigate the attack, and mitigate the effects of the attack on your business.',
  },
];
---

<section class="py-16 sm:py-20">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:max-w-7xl lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-8">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Frequently asked questions</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:col-span-2">
        <dl
          class="-mt-3"
          x-data="{ selected: null, toggle(value) { this.selected = this.selected === value ? null : value } }"
        >
          {
            questions.map((question, index) => (
              <div
                class="rounded-3xl px-4 transition"
                x-data={`{ id: ${index}, get isOpen() { return this.id === this.selected }, get isNextOpen() { return (this.id + 1) === this.selected } }`}
                x-bind:class="{ 'bg-primary-500/10 dark:bg-primary-400/10': isOpen }"
              >
                <dt
                  class="border-b text-lg transition"
                  x-cloak
                  x-bind:class="{ 'border-transparent': isOpen || isNextOpen, 'border-primary-900/10 dark:border-primary-300/10': !(isOpen || isNextOpen) }"
                >
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="group block w-full py-6 text-left transition focus-visible:outline-none"
                    aria-controls={question.id}
                    x-on:click="toggle(id)"
                    aria-expanded="false"
                    x-bind:aria-expanded="isOpen.toString()"
                  >
                    <div class="group-focus-visible:outline-primary-950 dark:group-focus-visible:outline-primary-200 flex items-center justify-between rounded-3xl group-focus-visible:outline group-focus-visible:outline-2 group-focus-visible:outline-offset-2">
                      <span class="font-medium">{question.title}</span>
                      <span class="ml-6 flex h-7 items-center">
                        <svg
                          class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 h-6 w-6 rotate-0 transform transition duration-200 ease-in-out"
                          x-bind:class="{ '-rotate-180': isOpen, 'rotate-0': !isOpen }"
                          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                          fill="currentColor"
                          aria-hidden="true"
                        >
                          <path d="M11.9997 13.1714L16.9495 8.22168L18.3637 9.63589L11.9997 15.9999L5.63574 9.63589L7.04996 8.22168L11.9997 13.1714Z" />
                        </svg>
                      </span>
                    </div>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd class="pb-6 pr-6" id={question.id} x-show="isOpen" x-cloak x-collapse>
                  <p class="text-primary-950/70 dark:text-primary-200/70 text-base">
                    {question.answer}
                  </p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
